{
  "info": {
    "name": "🎯 Mission-to-Coins Workflow (Outbox Pattern Demo)",
    "description": "Complete end-to-end workflow demonstrating the outbox pattern:\n\n**Mission → Coins in Wallet**\n\n## Flow:\n1. Create Mission Definition (50 COIN reward)\n2. Assign Mission to User\n3. User Submits Mission\n4. Admin Approves Submission\n5. ✨ MAGIC HAPPENS ✨\n   - Missions plugin emits MISSION_REWARD_GRANTED to outbox\n   - Outbox processor delivers event to wallet consumer\n   - Wallet consumer automatically credits 50 COIN\n   - User wallet balance updated in real-time\n6. Check Wallet Balance (should show 50 COIN!)\n7. View Transaction History (shows mission_reward)\n\n## Architecture:\n- **Event-Driven**: Missions and Wallet are decoupled\n- **Outbox Pattern**: Reliable event delivery\n- **Idempotent**: Safe to retry, no duplicate coins\n- **Double-Entry**: Full audit trail via ledger\n\n## Run This Collection:\n**Important:** Run the requests in order using the Collection Runner:\n1. Click \"Run\" button in Postman\n2. Select all requests\n3. Click \"Run Mission-to-Coins Workflow\"\n4. Watch the coins appear! 🪙\n\n---\n\nBased on:\n- specs/mission/missions.pillar.v2.yml\n- specs/wallet/wallet.pillar.v2.yml",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "admin_user_id",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "test_user_id",
      "value": "2",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "mission_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "assignment_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
